    <p style="padding-left: 150px;padding-right: 150px;">Fun Facts: The tallest structure in Japan was built as a broadcast, restaurant, and observation tower.  It is known as the tallest tower in the world and second tallest structure, just behind the Burj Khalifa.  Japan is known for having some of the most frequent earthquakes, so the Tokyo Skytree is earthquake resistant.  The building is colored for specific reasons: bluish white for a Japanese tradition, and illuminated, sky blue (chic, stylish) and purple (elegance, refinement).  At night, the two colors are alternated each day.  </p>
